{# src/_includes/pages/uganda-2026.njk #}

<!-- Hero -->
<section style="background:var(--bg-warm);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding-block:3.5rem 3rem;">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <p class="section-label">Coffee Origin Trip</p>
    <h1 style="max-width:640px;margin-bottom:.75rem;">Uganda, May 2–10, 2026</h1>
    <p style="font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--fg-mid);max-width:600px;margin-bottom:2rem;">
      A delegation of German specialty coffee roasters visits Uganda for nine days of farm visits, cuppings, and direct trade meetings — organised in partnership with CCPAU, Slow Food Uganda, and the Uganda Embassy Berlin.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:flex-start;margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
      <a href="/lot-info/" class="btn">Register as Supplier →</a>
      <a href="https://calendar.notion.so/meet/lorenzstckert/h932i4pxy" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a call</a>
    </div>
    <!-- Cooperation line -->
    <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:1rem;padding-top:1.75rem;border-top:1px solid var(--border);">
      <img src="/images/uganda-coat-of-arms.png" alt="Coat of Arms of Uganda" style="height:56px;width:auto;flex-shrink:0;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:.7rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--fg-light);margin-bottom:.2rem;">In cooperation with</div>
        <div style="font-size:.88rem;font-weight:600;color:var(--fg);line-height:1.4;">Ministry of Agriculture, Animal Industry and Fisheries (MAAIF) &amp;<br>Embassy of the Republic of Uganda, Berlin – Germany</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Key facts strip -->
<section style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);">
  <div class="wrapper" style="padding-block:1.75rem;">
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1.5rem;text-align:center;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);">9</div>
        <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--fg-light);margin-top:.2rem;">Days on origin</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);">8+</div>
        <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--fg-light);margin-top:.2rem;">Farms &amp; cooperatives</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);">5</div>
        <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--fg-light);margin-top:.2rem;">Growing regions</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);">10–50</div>
        <div style="font-size:.82rem;color:var(--fg-light);margin-top:.2rem;">Bags min. order</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Itinerary -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <p class="section-label">Programme</p>
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:2rem;">Day-by-Day Itinerary</h2>

    <div class="itinerary">

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">2 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Arrival in Entebbe</strong>
          <p>Transfer to Best Western Premier Hotel, Entebbe.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">3 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>NaCORI Labs &amp; Kituza Coffee Farm</strong>
          <p>Visit to the National Coffee Research Institute (NaCORI) mother gardens and labs, followed by Kituza Coffee Farm in Mukono. Stay: Best Western Premier, Entebbe.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">4 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Ministry of Agriculture · Kyarusozi Farm</strong>
          <p>Briefing at MAAIF (Ministry of Agriculture), press briefing, then travel to Kyarusozi for farm visit and the trade facilitation presentation. Stay: Nyaika Hotel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">5 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Queen Elizabeth National Park</strong>
          <p>Equator crossing at Kikolongo, Kazinga boat cruise, game drive. Stay: Parkview Safari Lodge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">6 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Africa Coffee Park, Rwashamaire</strong>
          <p>Full visit to Africa Coffee Park in Rwashamaire. Afternoon cattle experience at Emburara. Stay: Emburara Lodge.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">7 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Kiruhura Farm · Kabonera Farm, Masaka</strong>
          <p>Technical site tour at Kiruhura, then travel south to Kabonera farm and Victor's Farm in Masaka. Overnight in Kampala. Stay: Four Points Kampala.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">8 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Little Farms Coffee, Kakooge · Jinja</strong>
          <p>Farm visit at Kakooge, then travel to Jinja on the shores of Lake Victoria. Stay: Source of the Nile Hotel / Nile Village Hotel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">9 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Sera Wild Farm, Kapchorwa — High-Altitude Arabica</strong>
          <p>Drive to Kapchorwa on the slopes of Mount Elgon. Visit to Sera Wild Farm with high-altitude Arabica. Optional: Sipi Falls. Stay: Mount Elgon Hotel.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="itin-day">
        <div class="itin-date">10 May</div>
        <div class="itin-content">
          <strong>Final Cupping · Departure</strong>
          <p>Technical cupping session at UCD Lab (Lugogo), final debrief, transfer to Entebbe Airport.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Regions covered -->
<section class="section section-bg">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <p class="section-label">Origin regions</p>
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Farms &amp; Growing Areas</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(200px,1fr));gap:1rem;">
      {% set stops = [
        { name: "NaCORI Research Institute", region: "Mukono" },
        { name: "Kituza Coffee Farm", region: "Mukono" },
        { name: "Kyarusozi Farm", region: "Rwenzori" },
        { name: "Africa Coffee Park", region: "Rwashamaire" },
        { name: "Kiruhura Farm", region: "Kiruhura" },
        { name: "Kabonera / Victor's Farm", region: "Masaka" },
        { name: "Little Farms Coffee", region: "Kakooge / Luwero" },
        { name: "Sera Wild Farm", region: "Kapchorwa / Mt. Elgon" }
      ] %}
      {% for s in stops %}
        <div style="background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:var(--radius);padding:1rem 1.1rem;">
          <div style="font-weight:600;font-size:.9rem;">{{ s.name }}</div>
          <div style="font-size:.8rem;color:var(--accent);margin-top:.2rem;">{{ s.region }}</div>
        </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Partners -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <p class="section-label">Partners</p>
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">Who's behind this trip</h2>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fill,minmax(260px,1fr));gap:1.25rem;">
      <div class="step">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:.35rem;">CCPAU</h3>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:var(--fg-mid);margin:0;">Commercial Coffee Producers of Uganda — handles origin consolidation, lot aggregation, and international export logistics.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:.35rem;">Slow Food Uganda</h3>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:var(--fg-mid);margin:0;">Part of the international Slow Food movement, supporting good, clean and fair practices across Ugandan coffee farms.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:.35rem;">Uganda Embassy Berlin</h3>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:var(--fg-mid);margin:0;">Official diplomatic partner facilitating the delegation, introductions, and government-level briefings in Kampala.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom:.35rem;">Zuricaf / Lorenz Stöckert</h3>
        <p style="font-size:.875rem;color:var(--fg-mid);margin:0;">Trade facilitation, German import &amp; customs, key account management and quality assurance for the German roasters.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="section-bg" style="padding-block:var(--section-gap);">
  <div class="wrapper cta-block">
    <h2>Are you a Ugandan farmer or cooperative?</h2>
    <p>Submit your lot information now so the delegation can evaluate your coffee before the trip.</p>
    <div class="btn-group">
      <a href="/lot-info/" class="btn">Register as Supplier →</a>
      <a href="https://calendar.notion.so/meet/lorenzstckert/h932i4pxy" class="btn btn-outline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a call with Lorenz</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  /* Itinerary timeline */
  .itinerary { display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0; }
  .itin-day {
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:80px 1fr;
    gap:0 1.5rem;
    padding-block:.75rem;
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .itin-day:last-child { border-bottom:none; }
  .itin-date {
    font-size:.82rem;
    font-weight:700;
    color:var(--accent);
    padding-top:.2rem;
    white-space:nowrap;
    letter-spacing:.02em;
  }
  .itin-content strong { display:block;font-size:.95rem;margin-bottom:.2rem; }
  .itin-content p { font-size:.875rem;color:var(--fg-mid);margin:0; }

  /* Key facts strip responsive */
  @media (max-width:560px) {
    div[style*="repeat(4,1fr)"] { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr) !important; }
  }
</style>
